<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Public Sector Union Calls For Strike Action </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502202594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1426 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2502202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stuttgart (DDP/ADN) -- After the German White-Collar 
Union (DAG), the Public Service and Transport Workers' Union 
(OeTV) has now also called token strikes in all areas of public 
service. 
  Following four hours of talks by the wage negotiation 
committee, OeTV Chairwoman Monika Wulf-Mathies said this 
afternoon in Stuttgart that the token strikes are to take place 
on 28 February and 1 March in eastern and western Germany. In 
this way the union hopes to make the employers more open to 
negotiation at the fourth round on 9 and 10 March. There are to 
be token strikes at various sites throughout Germany. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

