<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Angolan President Arrives; To Meet Mitterrand </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502141494 Paris Radio France International in French 1230 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] President Jose Eduardo dos Santos of 
Angola is in France. He met Prime Minister Edouard Balladur, 
Cooperation Minister Michel Roussin, and Interior Minister 
Charles Pasqua yesterday. Today, the Angolan head of state will 
have lunch with Francois Mitterrand. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent Monique Mas] France will take part in the 
reconstruction of Angola, but with the help of all Angolans, 
including those who do not have any power. They will have to 
play a role in the country's political future, French 
Cooperation Minister Michel Roussin said. He added that before 
relaunching its cooperation [programs], the international 
community should make sure that any agreement between the 
government and UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence 
of Angola] be a stable one. [passage omitted] 
  The French interior minister wanted to clarify the situation 
about UNITA's friendship with France. It [the friendship] has 
been apparently replaced by state-to-state relations. However, 
the military embargo remains. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

