<H3> <TI>   Ciampi Sees `Worst' of Recession Over </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2602151794 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1200 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] [Correspondent Giulio 
Colavolpe] Trieste is a city that symbolizes Italian unity, and 
it is where a great, new, scientific machine -- the sincrotrone 
[as heard] -- has been unveiled. Carlo Azeglio Ciampi chose its 
inauguration to make an upbeat statement. 
  Just as the chaos surrounding the forthcoming elections 
seems 
to have reached its zenith, the prime minister has said that he 
has no doubts that the machinery has been set in motion and 
rather than giving up, Italy is on the path to recovery. 
  According to Ciampi the first signs of the recovery can 
already be seen: 
  [Begin Ciampi recording] What is certain is that the worst 
of the recession is behind us. There can be no doubts about 
this in Italy. Nor should the widespread uncertainty about the 
elections be mistaken for chaos -- it is an essential part of 
all true democracies. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

