<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guidelines for Participation in UN Actions Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2402120094 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1100 
GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2402120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Switzerland's defense and foreign ministers have 
come out in support of Swiss participation in peacekeeping 
missions by United Nations blue helmet troops. Kaspar Villiger 
and Flavio Cotti said such participation would be in line with 
Switzerland's tradition of supporting peaceful solutions for 
political conflicts. [Defense Minister] Mr. Villiger, speaking 
ahead of a national vote on the issue in June, said all Swiss 
blue helmet personnel would take part on a purely voluntary 
basis. He said the Swiss contingent would only take part in 
noncombat missions, that all parties in a conflict would have to 
agree to a UN deployment, and that Swiss troops could be 
withdrawn at any time. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-18150 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu039_m_94002" </HT>


