<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Condemns Massacre in Hebron </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502204794 Helsinki Radio Finland in English 1930 GMT 25 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Radio Finland </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finland's minister of foreign affairs, Heikki 
Haavisto, has deplored the massacre of Muslim worshippers in 
Hebron in the occupied West Bank. 
  In a statement issued on Friday [25 February], Foreign 
Minister Haavisto called the massacre a shocking act and 
expressed the hope that the act of violence would not endanger 
the Middle East peace process. He said that Finland expressed 
its deep condolences for the loss suffered by the Palestinians. 
Mr. Haavisto also said that he joins in the widespread hope 
that the shocking act will not encumber the peace process or the 
negotiations between Israel and the PLO. 

</TEXT>

