<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Opposition to EU Membership Weakening </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2702194994 Paris AFP in English 1933 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2702194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, Feb 27 (AFP) -- The number of Swedes in 
favour of European Union [EU] membership is growing, according 
to a new Temo public opinion poll published Sunday [27 February] 
as Sweden's EU membership negotiations drew to a close in 
Brussels. 
  According to the poll, which questioned 1,000 people in 
January and February, 35 percent were in favour of joining the 
EU, 42 percent were opposed and 23 percent were undecided. 
  The same poll conducted last September showed 29 percent in 
favour, 45 percent opposed and 26 percent undecided. 

</TEXT>

