<H3> <TI>   EU's Van den Broek `Optimistic' on FYROM Solution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2502211794 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 25 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC2502211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Takis Dhiamandis in Skopje] </F>
  [Excerpts] Before leaving for Skopje, Dutch European Union 
[EU] Commissioner Hans Van Den Broek said he is optimistic that 
a solution to the Athens-Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM] problem can be found. He also said he is 
concerned about the repercussions of the measures adopted by the 
Greek Government. [passage omitted] 
  Van Den Broek said that all problems, including the issue of 
the Greek measures, will be discussed in Brussels and he will 
brief the EU foreign ministers. 
  Referring to the Greek measures, Van Den Broek said the 
Greek 
side's arguments must also be examined and that this issue will 
be discussed in Brussels as soon as Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou's message is received. He stressed, however, that 
the solution of this problem will help resolve future tensions. 
  Generally, Van Den Broek said he is grateful for the 
cooperation he found as well as for the willingness to continue 
joint efforts to find a solution. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

