<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Steps To Enforce Sanctions Against FYROM Adopted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802062594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0500 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2802062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Long lines of tanker trucks carrying fuel have 
formed at the Kakavyia border checkpoint with Albania following 
the recent Finance Ministry decision to allow only five tanker 
trucks from Kakavyia and one from the checkpoint at 
Kristallopiyi to enter Albania. The Finance Ministry made its 
decision after the number of tanker trucks crossing the border 
to Albania increased following the adoption of the measures 
against Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM]. There are many signs that these trucks used 
Albanian territory as a route to Skopje. According to the 
Finance Ministry decision, Albania's daily fuel needs are fully 
covered by the six tanker trucks that go through every day. 

</TEXT>

