<H3> <TI>   Parliament Rejects Anti-Kemalist Motion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2502154794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1405 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2502154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Feb.25 (A.A) -- Deputy spokesman of 
parliament Vefa Tanir rejected a motion given by 12 deputies 
which demanded the restoring of the honor of a group of 
anti-Kemalists who were tried and executed 70 years ago as their 
plot to assassinate Turkey's leader Mustafa Kemal Ataturk has 
been brought into light. 
  Tanir sent a letter to fundamentalist Prosperity Party 
member 
Hasan Mezarci, who led 11 more deputies in the initiative, 
saying that, "your motion which attempts to degrade a certain 
period of the Turkish Grand National Assembly and Mustafa Kemal 
Ataturk, our great leader who has founded the Turkish state and 
republic and which, hurts the feelings of the public opinion, 
has been rejected, under article 68 of the parliamentary 
regulations." 
  Anti-Kemalist politician Hasan Mezarci, who announces in 
every occasion that he is against the secularist and democratic 
principles of Mustafa Kemal Ataturk, led eleven more deputies 
from various parties, in his initiative. 
  As the only True Path Party member in the motion, Melik 
Firat 
had been subjected to disciplinary action by his party just 
after the motion was handed to parliament, another signatory, 
Okkes Sendiller from Great Unity Party (UBP) decided to withdraw 
his name from the motion. 

</TEXT>

