<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Emergency Meeting Scheduled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2802111394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in Italian 1007 GMT 28 
Feb 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2802111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Bosnia: Downed Aircraft -- No NATO </F>
Meeting Scheduled for Now"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 28 Feb (ANSA) -- NATO sources have stated 
that no emergency meeting of the Atlantic Council has been 
scheduled for now to assess the situation in the wake of the 
downing of four Serbian aircraft this morning. 
  The sources explained that, on the basis of UN Security 
Council Resolution 816 of 1993, no special decisions whatsover 
have to be made prior to intercepting and/or downing aircraft. 

</TEXT>

