<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italian TV Reports NATO Fighters Took Off From Aviano </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802092894 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 0900 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We now have more details on the downing of the 
Serbian fighter planes. The NATO fighter planes that downed the 
Serbian planes took off from Aviano. The two F-16s took off at 
0530 and returned to the Italian base at 0600. According to 
information we have, six missiles were fired against the downed 
planes. One of the NATO F-16 planes downed three planes and the 
other downed the fourth one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-18191 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu039aa_94013" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-039 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  28 February 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Western Leaders Comment on Hebron Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   Spain Expresses `Profound Consternation' </H4>
<F P=102> LD2502173094 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 25 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Spanish Government, through the Diplomatic 
Information Office, has released a communique in which it 
expresses its profound consternation at the tragic massacre of 
Palestinians in the West Bank town of Hebron. The communique 
adds that the Spanish Government still believes that the peace 
process and the prompt application of the declaration of 
principles represent the only possible alternative in the face 
of the continuation of violence and clashes in the occupied 
territories. 
  The text also asks for a fresh effort from all the parties 
to 
restore a climate of harmony and calm, which will make it 
possible to achieve peace as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

