<H3> <TI>   Kohl Meets Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502212994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 2030 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502212994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Foreign Minister Mahmud Va'ezi, the special 
envoy of our country's president has held a meeting with Helmut 
Kohl, the German chancellor. In the meeting, a written message 
from President Hashemi-Rafsanjani was submitted to the German 
chancellor. 
  The German chancellor welcomed the expansion of ties between 
Iran and Germany and, expressing satisfaction about the current 
situation, conveyed his wish to improve and expand the relations 
between the Islamic Republic of Iran and the European Community. 
  The special envoy of our country's president, for his part, 
noted that the good relations between the Islamic Republic of 
Iran and Germany can prove to be a suitable gateway toward the 
consolidation and expansion of relations between the Islamic 
Republic of Iran and the European Community. 

</TEXT>

