<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry: Israel Must Prevent Further Violence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2502163594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1529 GMT 
25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2502163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "We expect the Israeli Government to adopt all 
necessary measures to prevent further bloodshed." This was 
stated by the Foreign Ministry, which added that "increased 
vigilance and a heightened sense of responsibility" are 
necessary following the Hebron massacre. 
  A statement from the Foreign Ministry stresses that "we must 
make sure extremist fanaticism does not jeopardize the progress 
made toward peace." 
  The statement further says that acts of "extremists on all 
sides" against normally defenseless citizens are aimed at 
dashing the hopes for peace. 

</TEXT>

