<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Sees `No Developments' in Proximity Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702171794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said that so far there 
have been no developments in the proximity talks for the 
implementation of the confidence-building measures [CBM's]. In 
a statement made in Makhairas after a memorial service for 
Grigorios Avxendiou, Kliridhis said that in his first report the 
UN secretary general will not say much. He added that the 
report will say that both sides have accepted the UN secretary 
general's proposals in principle and will call on them to 
intensify their efforts so that a way to implement the CBM's is 
found. 
  Kliridhis said that Butrus-Ghali will attribute 
responsibilities, if any, in his next report, which will be 
submitted three weeks after the first one. Responding to a 
question, the president said that he will not go to Athens now 
because there is nothing new. 

</TEXT>

