<H3> <TI>   Cetin: `Legitimate Act' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2802192094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has said that the 
downing of four Serbian planes by NATO over Bosnia-Herzegovina 
is a legitimate act carried out while implementing UN 
resolutions. 
  Cetin, who is in New Zealand, assessed the latest 
developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina for Turkish Radio and 
Television. 
  [Begin Cetin recording] From the beginning, we supported all 
the resolutions made for a lasting and just peace, and we 
believed that these resolutions must be implemented effectively. 
There were reports at a certain stage that not all the heavy 
weapons which were supposed to withdraw 20 kms in line with the 
NATO resolution were under UN control. At the time we warned 
the United Nations and NATO that if these weapons were not 
placed under full UN control they could be used in other places. 
It is now understood that the cease-fire achieved around 
Sarajevo can be violated, and the weapons, unless placed under 
UN control, can be taken to other places. Consequently, in 
order to achieve lasting peace, NATO and the UN Security Council 
must continue with their actions in a determined way. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

