<H3> <TI>   Sweden Agrees on Terms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103113894 Paris AFP in English 1122 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0103113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, March 1 (AFP) -- The European Union has 
reached agreement with Sweden on that country's terms for 
joining the Union, an EU spokesman said here Tuesday [1 March]. 
  The announcement came after 25 hours of non-stop 
negotiations 
on the terms for taking Sweden, along with Austria, Finland and 
Norway, into the Union on January 1, 1995. 
  Sweden was pushing for a gradual phase-in of its 
contributions to the EU budget. 
  The year-old negotiations were supposed to have been wrapped 
up at midnight Monday after a final four-day session that 
started on Friday. 

</TEXT>

