<H3> <TI>   Belgian Reinforcements To Be Stationed in Vitez </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0103105894 Brussels BELGA in French 1839 GMT 28 Feb 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0103105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed GGD/RHR: "Bosnia: Belgian Reinforcements </F>
Will Be Going Very Close to Vitez"; as released by Brussels 
BELGA Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 28 Feb (BELGA) -- The additional 150 
Belgian UN troops sent to Bosnia-Herzegovina will be stationed 
in the region of Vitez (in central Bosnia, 45 kilometers 
northwest of Sarajevo) confirmed a military source on Monday 
night [28 February]. 
  The precise location of their camp has not yet been decided, 
added a spokesman for the Defense Ministry. 
  Around 100 Belgian troops are already based in Vitez. They 
belong to a transport company (comprising 102 men) entrusted 
with getting humanitarian aid through to the civilian 
population. This company is part of the Belgian-Netherlands 
battalion. The troops have dubbed the present operation "Moving 
Star." 
  The armored infantry company sent from Croatia as 
reinforcements will participate in monitoring the cease-fire 
agreement concluded last Wednesday between the Croats and the 
Muslims, which provides for the deployment of UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces] troops along a front line 350-km long. In 
the area around Vitez, the fighting had involved Muslims and 
Croats. 

</TEXT>

