<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Received DM4 Million From SED </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202142394 Munich FOCUS in German 21 Feb 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Four Million for Russia's </F>
Right-Winger"] 
  [Text] The suspicion that Werner Girke, the former 
administrator of the foreign assets of the Socialist Unity Party 
of Germany [SED], illegally transferred party funds to Russian 
nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy is hardening. Girke, 
who is now employed by the Trust Agency, worked as trustee for 
the SED holding company Orvag since 1991. He is the owner of 
the Orvag subsidiary TVO (Trustee, Administration, and 
Organization company). Meanwhile one knows for sure that a 
financial adviser to the leader of the Russian nationalists 
stayed at TVO for many weeks in the fall of 1993. Another piece 
of evidence is that, after they had met in Austria, a second 
meeting between Girke and Zhirinovskiy took place in Slovenia in 
mid-January. 
  When the premises of Girke's company were searched in early 
January documents were seized that prove that he embezzled 4 
million German marks [DM] from SED foreign assets. Meanwhile, 
the Trust Agency has found out that Girke invested the money in 
companies in Moscow. To what extent the enterprises are 
connected with Zhirinovskiy is currently the subject of 
investigations by the Central Investigations Office for 
Government- and Unification-Related Crime (ZERV). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

