<H3> <TI>   Algerian Aircraft Hijacked to Alicante </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802132194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Algerian aircraft is being held at l'Altet 
airport in Alicante, apparently hijacked by one or several 
persons. The latest details from Rafael Bermejo. 
  [Bermejo] Good afternoon. Sources at Alicante airport have 
confirmed to Radio Nacional de Espana the presence of the 
Algerian airlines -- Air Algerie -- aircraft at this airport. 
It is now known that it is a Boeing 727, registration 7TVB. 
The aircraft was reportedly on a domestic flight in Algeria, 
and according to various sources -- without official 
confirmation yet -- the hijackers are supposedly three in 
number, and they are in constant touch with Alicante airport. 
The number of passengers on the hijkacked aircraft is not known 
at present. 

