<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army General Arrested on Terrorist Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802224594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2218 GMT 
28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802224594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Romolo Mangani has been arrested by officers 
from the Division for General Investigations for Special 
Operations who were implementing an arrest warrant issued by 
Deputy Prosecutors Galasso and Piro as part of the investigation 
into a plot, among other things, to the storm RAI [Italian 
Broadcasting Corporation]'s offices at Saxa Rubra, near Rome. 
  The charges on the warrant are those of political 
conspiracy. 
General Mangani was the commander of the III ROC [NATO regional 
operation center] based at Martinafranca. His name also came up 
as part of the inquiry in the Ustica disaster. 

</TEXT>

