<H3> <TI>   Bonn Promises Economic Cooperation to Azerbaijan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103182694 Hamburg DPA in German 1529 GMT 1 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0103182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The FRG Government has promised 
Azerbaijan economic cooperation if the Asian country settles the 
conflict with neighboring Armenia over the enclave of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. According to a spokesman of the Development 
Ministry, this was made clear by Bonn Development Minister 
Carl-Dieter Stranger (Christian Social Union) during a meeting 
with Azerbaijani Foreign Minister Hasan Hasanov in Bonn on 
Tuesday [1 March]. Spranger called on the government in Baku to 
embark upon a course of democratic reforms. 
  Hasanov was, however, not able to talk to his host, FRG 
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel. The negotiations about European 
Union membership in Brussels forced Kinkel to cancel all his 
foreign policy appointments on Tuesday at short notice. 
Hungarian Prime Minister Peter Boross, who paid a first visit 
to Chancellor Helmut Kohl, also had to do without the planned 
meeting in the Foreign Ministry. 

