<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Italy &amp; Vatican City </F>
<H3> <TI>   Andreatta Meets Somali Salvation Democratic Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2402140494 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1615 GMT 23 
Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2402140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Somalia/Italy: Andreatta Meets </F>
Somali Salvation Democratic Front Leader"] 
  [Text] Rome, 23 Feb (ANSA) -- Foreign Minister Beniamino 
Andreatta on Wednesday [23 February] received the military 
leader of the Somali Salvation Democratic Front (SSDF), Colonel 
Abdullahi Yusuf, to discuss developments in Somalia and the 
security of foreign development aid workers there, a communique 
announced. 
  Andreatta and Yusuf, said the communique, agreed on the need 
to support national reconciliation efforts and that warring 
Somali factions must be the ones to identify acceptable forms of 
future contacts. 
  Andreatta stressed that after Western contingents withdraw 
from Somalia, leaving fewer United Nations troops in the 
country, international aid efforts will be forced to be directed 
to more secure areas where "pacification is more advanced." He 
also warned that Italian aid will continue only if guarantees 
are given on the safety of Italians. 
  Yusuf reportedly assured Andreatta that the SSDF, of the 
northern Mijurtin clan and one of the two strongest military 
forces in Somalia, will provide these guarantees. 
  The ministry described the talks as cordial. They followed a 
tour by Italian Foreign Undersecretary Carmelo Azzara' in the 
Horn of Africa last week, when he also met Somali warlord 
General Aideed in Nairobi, Kenya. 
  Although the SSDF has been at war with Aideed's clan since 
the fall of dictator Mohammed Siad Barre in January 1991, Yusuf 
in May of last year began talks with Aideed, talks which were 
not officially sponsored by the political wing of the party, led 
by SSDF president Mohammed Abshir. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

