<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO's Woerner: `We Cannot Tolerate Violations' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103134094 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1200 
GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with NATO Secretary General Manfred Woerner by </F>
Francesco Mattioli; place and date not given -- both Woerner and 
Mattioli speak in English with superimposed Italian 
translation--recorded] 
  [Text] Following the punishment inflicted on the Serbs we 
have seen an increase in NATO's credibility: This is the view of 
NATO Secretary General Manfred Woerner, who was interviewed by 
RAIDUE news correspondent, Francesco Mattioli. 
  [Mattioli] A clear-skies policy over Bosnia has been in 
force 
for months and it has been violated hundreds of times, why has 
NATO decided to react right now? 
  [Woerner] It has not been violated -- as you say -- hundreds 
of times. This is the first violation by jets. We tolerated 
violations of the policy by helicopters because from a military 
point of view they were not significant. These were 
jet-fighters and furthermore our pilots saw them bomb targets on 
the ground. 
  [Mattioli] This was the first military engagement for a 
military alliance that has existed for 45 years, how do you feel? 
  [Woerner] Of course it is always preferable to avoid using 
force. In general we want to achieve our objectives without 
using force. However, we cannot tolerate violations of UN 
decisions using force, and so we went from words to actions. We 
are determined and I believe we have given a basic lesson that 
means that now everyone must take NATO seriously. 
  [Mattioli] Do you not fear that the war will be extended? 
  [Woerner] No, not at all, in fact it is more likely that the 
opposite will happen. I believe that in the future the no-fly 
zone will be respected. 

</TEXT>

