<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Hails Success of EU Talks in Brussels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203111094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1023 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0203111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN): German Chancellor Helmut Kohl today 
welcomed the results of the Brussels talks on the accession to 
the European Union of Sweden, Finland, and Austria, as well as 
the progress of negotiations with Norway, calling them a "great 
success for Europe." According to government spokesman Dieter 
Vogel, Kohl said during a cabinet meeting in Bonn today that the 
accession of these countries would go down as a major event in 
European history. All parties could be "more than satisfied" 
with the results of the talks. 
  Kohl emphasized that the German Government, which had 
spearheaded the opening of the European Community towards 
southern Europe, had a "decisive interest" in the Scandinavian 
countries and Austria becoming members. Germany's close 
cooperation with the new member states would be of great benefit 
to Germany in particular, he said. 

</TEXT>

