<DOCNO> FBIS3-18365 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu041_h_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-041 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visit by Hungarian Prime Minister Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Seeks EU Membership </H4>
<F P=102> LD0103220994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
2100 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103220994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] [Announcer] Prime Minister Peter Boross has 
ended his visit to Germany end started on his return journey. 
Gyorgy Bernat reports from Bonn. 
  [Begin Bernat recording] Hungary is to submit its request 
for admission to the European Union [EU] in April, Peter Boross 
told Hungarian journalists today in Bonn. This was also 
discussed during the talks between the Hungarian prime minister 
and Chancellor Kohl. Later, the head of the German Government 
said publicly that this was not just a symbolic but a very wise 
decision indeed. [passage omitted] 
  Peter Boross is to meet Helmut Kohl again soon who will 
visit 
Budapest on 15 April at the invitation of the prime minister. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

