<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Warns Strikes Could Destroy Upswing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2802150194 Hamburg BILD in German 28 Feb 94 pp 1-2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2802150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Waste Disposal, Railroads, Post, </F>
Banks -- Strike Chaos as of Today"] 
  [Excerpts] Now OeTV [Public Sector, Transportation, and 
Traffic Trade Union] Chairwoman Monika Wulf-Mathies (51) is also 
taking up the strike hammer -- two days of warning strikes, 
which will affect us all. [passage omitted] Yesterday 
Chancellor Kohl and Foreign Minister Kinkel, Free Democratic 
Party of Germany [FDP], warned against strikes. 
  Economics Minister Guenther Rexrodt (FDP) told BILD: "I warn 
against destroying the nascent upswing through strikes and 
against deliberately trampling on the sprouting plant of 
economic development. Strike means a stop to the economic 
upswing and many thousands of unemployed at short notice. I 
appeal to the partners to the wage negotiations: You must 
finally approach each other and agree on flexible contracts, 
tailor-made for the different branches, regions, and problems of 
the companies. Think about the fact that we are all sitting in 
the same boat. I tell the helmsmen of the employers and trade 
unions: Either we want to reach the shore together or we will 
all sink." 

</TEXT>

